Yes, I also made this patched `_label`. The property params of `@{property_name}.setter` should be `property_name`. Maybe we can improve it like this:

```python
def _label(definition):
    if definition.type in ('function', 'method'):
        def_code = definition.get_line_code(1)
        setter_name = definition.name + '.setter'
        if '@property' in def_code:
            params = ''
        elif ('@' + setter_name) in def_code:
            params = setter_name
        else:
            params = ', '.join(param.name for param in definition.params)
        return '{}({})'.format(definition.name, params)

    return definition.name
```

